{"id":"252239678_Complexity_of_Null-and_Positivstellensatz_Proofs","abstract":"We introduce two versions of proof systems dealing with systems of inequalities: Positivstellensatz refutations and Positivstellensatz cal-culus. For both systems we prove the lower bounds on degrees and lengths of derivations for the example due to Lazard, Mora and Philip-pon. These bounds are sharp, as well as they are for the Nullstellen-satz refutations and for the polynomial calculus. The bounds demon-strate a gap between the Null-and Positivstellensatz refutations on one hand, and the polynomial calculus and Positivstellensatz calculus on the other.","authors":["Dima Grigoryev","Nicolai Vorobjov"],"meta":["December 2001Annals of Pure and Applied Logic 113(1-3):153-160","DOI:10.1016/S0168-0072(01)00055-0"],"references":["242371169_Cones_of_Matrices_and_Set-Functions_and_0-1_Optimization","239060870_Nullstellensatz_lower_bounds_for_Tseitin_tautologies","226674080_Complexity_Of_Positivstellensatz_Proofs_For_The_Knapsack","221498675_Lower_Bounds_on_Hilbert's_Nullstellensatz_and_Propositional_Proofs","220467833_Proof_Complexity_In_Algebraic_Systems_And_Bounded_Depth_Frege_Systems_With_Modular_Counting","3801355_Linear_gaps_between_degrees_for_the_polynomial_calculus_modulodistinct_primes","3593076_Lower_bounds_on_Hilbert's_Nullstellensatz_and_propositional_proofs","2610381_Using_the_Groebner_basis_algorithm_to_find_proofs_of_unsatisfiability","268018664_On_the_complexity_of_propositional_calculus","256079433_Linear_Gaps_Between_Degrees_for_the_Polynomial_Calculus_Modulo_Distinct_Primes","247435449_Roy_Dynamical_method_in_algebra_E_ective_Nullstel-lenslouatze","243767085_On_a_Representation_of_the_Matching_Polytope_Via_Semidefinite_Liftings","243763350_Bounds_for_the_degrees_in_the_NullstellensatzAnnals_of_Math_126_577-591","228005946_The_Positivstellensatz_and_Small_Deduction_Rules_for_Systems_of_Inequalities","226311514_Lower_Bounds_for_the_polynomial_calculus_and_the_Groebner_basis_alg